quran[3]{c,v,t,f}:
  2,43,"And establish prayer and give zakāh{1} and bow with those who bow [in worship and obedience].",footnotes:1:[An annual expenditure for the benefit of the Islāmic community (see 9:60) required of those Muslims who have excess wealth. Prayer and zakāh are among the pillars of Islām.]
  2,44,"Do you order righteousness of the people and forget{1} yourselves while you recite the Scripture? Then will you not reason?",footnotes:1:[Make exceptions of.]
  2,45,"And seek help through patience and prayer; and indeed, it is difficult except for the humbly submissive [to Allāh]"